    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-01T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-01T10:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-01T17:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 1, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 1—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. Department’s 28, May [<hi rend="italic">April</hi>] 30, 4 p.m. The Prime
                    Minister has requested me to telegraph a message in the following sense to be
                    transmitted to ex-Ambassador Morgenthau: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Prime Minister appreciates Mr. Morgenthau’s interest in Greece and
                            wishes to thank him. The Government’s policy is directed toward internal
                            peace and friendship between the political parties and every effort is
                            being exerted to achieve that purpose. The Government is doing its best
                            to the end that sanctions may be as few as possible.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
